In this article, it is reported that President Obama met with the House Democratic Caucus to discuss the ongoing government shutdown. The President thanked the House Democrats for their support of a clean, short-term continuing resolution that would reopen the government. He urged the Republican Leadership to allow the bill passed by the Senate to have an up or down vote, which he believes would pass with bipartisan support and end the shutdown. The President and the House Democrats emphasized their belief that one faction of the Republicans should not be able to demand a ransom for Congress doing its job and paying the bills. The President also expressed his desire to engage with both sides on a broader budget agreement that focuses on job creation, economic growth, and a strong middle class. He thanked the House Democrats for their support in promoting policies that benefit working families and provide opportunities for success.